Under ubuntu, make rpm package for libcustomized_3a

*****************************************************
Prerequisite for build RPM package:

Install rpmbuild under ubuntu if needed,
sudo apt-get install rpm

Install auto-make utils needed for building the rpm from source,
sudo apt-get install autoconf libtool

*****************************************************
Build RPM for libcustomized_3a:

Run the shell script under this directory to build rpm in this
directory.

./build_rpm.sh

*****************************************************
Install the built RPM:

Install under default directories /usr/lib64, /usr/include and /etc as below,

sudo rpm -ivh libcustomized_3a-xxx.x86_64.rpm --nodeps

Or, relocatable install, like below,

rpm -ivh --noparentdirs --relocate /etc=/your/own/dir --relocate /usr=/your/own/dir libcustomized_3a-1.0.0-2.x86_64.rpm
